abstract: “Love & Air Sex,” which follows two couples whose relationships have recently dissolved, is set in a city teeming with singles and air sex competitions.
snippet: “Love & Air Sex,” which follows two couples whose relationships have recently dissolved, is set in a city teeming with singles and air sex competitions.
lead_paragraph: Under its contemporary facade of buzzing cellphones and potty-mouthed insults, Bryan Poyser’s “Love & Air Sex” is a traditional romantic comedy that is desperate to please. Although the main characters, in their 20s and early 30s, communicate mostly via text message, often in sexually graphic detail, they are the same vulnerable relationship seekers they have always been but with extra mileage on their pedometers.

abstract: The opera “Brokeback Mountain,” based on the short story by Annie Proulx, opened at the Teatro Real in Madrid.
snippet: The opera “Brokeback Mountain,” based on the short story by Annie Proulx, opened at the Teatro Real in Madrid.
lead_paragraph: MADRID — When the news came five years ago that Charles Wuorinen was writing an opera based on “Brokeback Mountain,” the 1997 Annie Proulx short story that was made into an Oscar-winning film in 2005, it seemed at first a baffling mismatch of composer and subject. Mr. Wuorinen, 75, built his reputation as and remains an unabashedly complex Modernist. “Brokeback Mountain” is the immensely sad tale of the impossible love between two Wyoming cowboys.

abstract: While the National Football League season is about to end, EA Sports is preparing the next version of its Madden NFL video game, adding new movements recorded using stunt players.
snippet: While the National Football League season is about to end, EA Sports is preparing the next version of its Madden NFL video game, adding new movements recorded using stunt players.
lead_paragraph: BURNABY, British Columbia — The football players strutted down a 40-yard strip of synthetic turf, yelling, jumping and flailing their arms to whip the fans into a frenzy. But there was no stadium and no crowd here on this recent day, only a barnlike studio with an animator directing the mock celebration and a few computer technicians recording the movements with dozens of high-speed motion-capture cameras that zero in on 65 reflective markers Velcroed to the players’ uniforms.

abstract: Over two days Fredrick Brennan, 19, who uses a wheelchair, had nearly $5,000 stolen from him, helped the police identify the thief, and was left to get home on his own during a winter storm.
snippet: Over two days Fredrick Brennan, 19, who uses a wheelchair, had nearly $5,000 stolen from him, helped the police identify the thief, and was left to get home on his own during a winter storm.
lead_paragraph: Fredrick Brennan, 19, moved out of his mother’s home in New Jersey in August and into an apartment in Brooklyn that his boss helped him find. This leap was far greater than the 120 miles or so on a map.
